Collects Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) join, Primary Refresh Token (PRT), MDM enrollment, and Intune diagnostic information into a timestamped log file for troubleshooting device registration and auto-enrollment issues.

Detailed Description

This PowerShell script performs a non-invasive diagnostic assessment of a Windows device's Microsoft Entra ID and Intune enrollment status by:

Creating a timestamped diagnostic log file in the Public user profile.
Collecting and recording:
dsregcmd /status output
MDM auto-enrollment policy settings
Enrollment registry configuration
OMADM account information
Retrieving recent authentication events from:
Microsoft Entra ID Operational logs
Retrieving recent device enrollment events from:
Device Management Enterprise Diagnostics Provider (DMEDP) logs
Performing a quick health assessment of:
Azure AD Primary Refresh Token (PRT) status
Azure AD user registration state
MDM enrollment URL presence
Consolidating all findings into a single text report for analysis.
What It Checks
Entra ID device registration status
Azure AD Join state
Hybrid Join indicators
Primary Refresh Token (PRT) availability
Intune auto-enrollment policy configuration
MDM enrollment records
OMADM account registration
Authentication failures and token issues
Device enrollment failures and MDM errors




# =========================================
# FIXED Entra / Intune Diagnostic Script
# READ ONLY - safe
# =========================================

$LogFile = "$env:PUBLIC\MDM_Diag_FIXED_$(Get-Date -Format yyyyMMdd_HHmmss).txt"

function Section($t) {
    "`n====================" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
    $t | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
    "====================" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
}

function Run($cmd) {
    "`n> $cmd`n" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
    cmd /c $cmd 2>&1 | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
}

Section "1. DSREGCMD STATUS"
Run "dsregcmd /status"

Section "2. MDM AUTO-ENROLLMENT POLICY"
Run "reg query HKLM\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\MDM"

Section "3. ENROLLMENT REGISTRY STATE"
Run "reg query HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Enrollments"
Run "reg query HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Provisioning\OMADM\Accounts"

Section "4. AAD AUTH LOGS (PRT / WAM ISSUES)"
Get-WinEvent -LogName "Microsoft-Windows-AAD/Operational" -MaxEvents 100 |
Select TimeCreated, Id, Message |
Out-String | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append

Section "5. DEVICE ENROLLMENT LOGS (THIS IS CRITICAL)"
Get-WinEvent -LogName "Microsoft-Windows-DeviceManagement-Enterprise-Diagnostics-Provider/Admin" `
-ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -MaxEvents 100 |
Select TimeCreated, Id, LevelDisplayName, Message |
Out-String | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append

Section "6. QUICK STATE CHECK"

$ds = dsregcmd /status 2>&1 | Out-String

$prt = if ($ds -match "AzureAdPrt\s*:\s*YES") {"YES"} else {"NO"}
$aad = if ($ds -match "IsUserAzureAD\s*:\s*YES") {"YES"} else {"NO"}
$mdm = if ($ds -match "MDMUrl\s*:\s*(.+)") {"FOUND"} else {"MISSING"}

"AzureAdPrt: $prt" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
"IsUserAzureAD: $aad" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append
"MDMUrl: $mdm" | Tee-Object -FilePath $LogFile -Append

Write-Host "`nDONE - Log saved to $LogFile" -ForegroundColor Green
